<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How much search traffic comes from AI?</strong></p>
<p>AI referral traffic currently accounts for about 1.08% of all website traffic, per <a href="https://www.conductor.com/academy/aeo-geo-benchmarks-report/">Conductor's 2026 benchmarks</a>. The volume grew 527% year over year. ChatGPT drives 87% of that traffic. Despite the small share, AI visitors convert at 14.2% compared to 2.8% for traditional organic visitors.</p>
<p><strong>What percentage of Google searches trigger AI Overviews?</strong></p>
<p>Approximately 50% of U.S. searches now trigger an AI Overview. Globally, the rate is closer to 25%. Informational queries trigger AI Overviews 99.2% of the time. Commercial and transactional queries trigger them far less frequently.</p>
<p><strong>Do AI Overviews reduce organic clicks?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Organic CTR drops 61% on queries where AI Overviews appear. Position 1 CTR fell from 7.3% to 2.6% in one year. However, being cited within an AI Overview produces 35% more organic clicks than not being cited at all.</p>
<p><strong>How do I get cited by AI search engines?</strong></p>
<p>Focus on long-form content (2,900+ words), include statistics and citations, update content every 60 days, and build <a href="/blog/domain-authority-guide/">domain authority</a>. Listicle format earns a 25% citation rate, the highest of any content type. <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">Schema markup</a> and structured answers also increase citation likelihood.</p>
<p><strong>Is AI search replacing Google?</strong></p>
<p>Not yet. Google still handles 77.9% of all digital queries. But ChatGPT holds 17.1% and growing. Among Gen Z, 66% use ChatGPT for research compared to 69% using Google. The gap is narrowing, especially for informational and creative queries.</p>
<p><strong>How fast is AI search traffic growing?</strong></p>
<p>AI referral traffic grows 165x faster than traditional organic search. Year-over-year growth exceeded 527%. During the 2025 holiday season, AI referral traffic surged 693%. The trajectory points to AI referrals representing 20 to 28% of all web referral traffic by end of 2026.</p>
<p>AI search is no longer a future trend. It is a current reality reshaping how people find information and how businesses earn traffic. The statistics above represent a snapshot of March 2026. These numbers will change. We update this page as new data becomes available.</p>
